<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1010185>
    dc:description "PLATE 9. Craspedophorus strachani group, C. ruficrus complex. Elytra (left humerus from oblique view): Fig. 61 c. C. glaber Bates, 1886, male, Cameroon; Fig. 67 b. C. ruficrus (Chaudoir, 1861) female Guinea Equatorial. Fig. 68 b. C. lemariei n. sp. HT (male); Fig. 69 b; C. dicranulothorax n. sp., HT (female). Fig. 72. Pronotum in different species of the C. strachani group (design), a-c. C. strachani s. str. subgroup, d, e) C. muata subgroup." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1010185/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1010207>
    dc:description "FIGURE 135. Distribution of the Craspedophorus strachani group (II) in the Afrotropical Region. A) 1 – 3 C. ruficrus (Chaudoir, 1861): 1) Cameroon, South: Grand Batanga; 2) “ Rio Muni, Biafra ” (= Guinea Equatorial, Litoral): San Juan Cape; 3) “ Gabon français ” (= Gabon, HT); B) C. dicranulothorax n. sp.: 4) Cameroon, Southwest: Buea (HT). C) 5 – 7 C. glaber Bates, 1886: 5) Cameroon, Centre: Yaoundé; 6) Southwest (HT): ne Bakingili; 7) “ Old Calabar ”. (= Calabar, southeastern Nigeria: Cross River). D) C. lafertei Murray, 1857: 8 (= 7) “ Old Calabar ”. E) C. lemariei n. sp.: 9) Gabon, “ Lac Zonanghé ” (= Onangue Lake, Moyen-Ogooué); F) 10 – 12 C. phenacoides n. sp.: 10) Cameroon, Centre: Mbalmayo env.; 11) East: Lomie env., PT; Littoral: Edéa env., HT." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1010207/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1010175>
    dc:description "PLATE 4. Specimens of C. strachani group I-III, underside. 28. C. klugii (Hope, 1842) female: dorsal habitus (left), ventrites (right); 29. C. klugii (Hope, 1842) male (HT): dorsal habitus (left), ventrites (right); 30. C. tetrastigma milzi (Duvivier, 1891) male: dorsal habitus (left), ventrites (right); 31 a. C. latipennis Burgeon, 1930, male: dorsal habitus (left), ventrites (right); b. left metepisterum, oblique ventral view; 32. C. strachani strachani (Hope, 1842) HT (male): dorsal habitus (left), detail with aedeagus (right); 33 a. C. latemaculatus Alluaud, 1930 HT (female): dorsal habitus (left), ventrites (right); b. left metepisternum, oblique ventral view; left metepisternum outined in yellow." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1010175/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

